 Listing collections succeeds against a vanilla 4.0.10 server.

Currently when ismaster fails, the exception class is not logged. For example, the driver can produce this message when it is instructed to use a nonexistent path with ssl_ca_cert option:

{code}
MONGODB | Error running ismaster on localhost:27741: system lib
{code}

The "system lib" part is coming from openssl. With the exception class included, the message looks like this which immediately identifies the source of the problem:

{code}
MONGODB | Error running ismaster on localhost:27741: OpenSSL::X509::StoreError: system lib
{code}

This situation was encountered by a SO user in https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58053353/ibmcloud-how-can-i-connect-to-mongodb/58071056.

The driver documents (https://docs.mongodb.com/ruby-driver/master/tutorials/ruby-driver-create-client) :auth_source to be of a String type. However, the driver uses :external symbol to represent the $external auth source. This symbol, when passed to the server, fails x509 auth as follows:

{code}
D, [2019-09-04T17:38:05.105657 #20412] DEBUG -- : MONGODB | localhost:32101 | external.authenticate | FAILED | wrong type for field ($db) symbol != string (13111) | 0.000392059s
{code}

Eliminating the conversion from $external to :external makes x509 auth work.

Currently all of the code for the C extension is in a single file, and is hard to work with. To make the code more readable:

- Separate files are to be created for reading, writing, utility and initialization methods;
- The functions in each file are to be grouped according to what kind of data they operate on;
- The grouping of functions is to be consistent between read and write files.
